The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Exide net profit surges 62%

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Jan. 18: Exide Industries has posted a 62 per cent rise in net profit in the third quarter at Rs 34.8 crore compared with Rs 21.5 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

 Its sales rose 34 per cent to Rs 457.7 crore from Rs 341.6 crore in the same period last year. The companys earnings per Re 1 face value share is 50 paise compared with 30 paise during the corresponding period of the previous financial year.

 The good performance of the city-based company came at a time when international lead prices, the input behind its product, has risen significantly.

 S.B Ganguly, executive chairman and chief executive of Exide, said lead prices went up by 32 per cent during the quarter.

 But we also managed to pass on some of it, 10 per cent to be precise, in the replacement market, Ganguly added. 

 Buoyed by the result, the Exide stock gained 2.68 per cent, or Rs 1.15, to Rs 44.05 on a volatile BSE. 




